<h2>Beginning Bayes in R</h2>
<div id="introduction-to-bayesian-thinking" class="section level3">
<h3>Introduction to Bayesian thinking</h3>
<pre class="r"><code>library(TeachBayes)</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>areas &lt;- c(2,1,2,1,2)
spinner_plot(areas)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /></p>
<pre class="r"><code>spinner_probs(areas)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##   Region  Prob
## 1      1 0.250
## 2      2 0.125
## 3      3 0.250
## 4      4 0.125
## 5      5 0.250</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>df = data.frame(Region = 1:5, areas, Probability = areas/sum(areas))

df</code></pre>
<pre><code>##   Region areas Probability
## 1      1     2       0.250
## 2      2     1       0.125
## 3      3     2       0.250
## 4      4     1       0.125
## 5      5     2       0.250</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>spins = spinner_data(areas, 1000)


<!--more-->"

bar_plot(spins)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /></p>
<pre class="r"><code>S = summarise(group_by(data.frame(Region=spins),Region), N=n())
S</code></pre>
<pre><code>## # A tibble: 5 x 2
##   Region     N
##    &lt;int&gt; &lt;int&gt;
## 1      1   279
## 2      2   130
## 3      3   219
## 4      4   128
## 5      5   244</code></pre>
<p>Construct frequency table of spins:</p>
<pre class="r"><code>table(spins)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## spins
##   1   2   3   4   5 
## 279 130 219 128 244</code></pre>
<p>Find fraction of spins equal to 2:</p>
<pre class="r"><code>mean(spins==2 )</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] 0.13</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>bayes_df = data.frame(Model=paste(&quot;Spinner&quot;, c(&quot;A&quot;,&quot;B&quot;,&quot;C&quot;,&quot;D&quot;))) 

bayes_df$Prior = rep(0.25,4)

bayes_df$Likelihood = round(c(1/3,1/2,1/4,1/6),2)

bayes_df = bayesian_crank(bayes_df)

bayes_df</code></pre>
<pre><code>##       Model Prior Likelihood Product Posterior
## 1 Spinner A  0.25       0.33  0.0825     0.264
## 2 Spinner B  0.25       0.50  0.1250     0.400
## 3 Spinner C  0.25       0.25  0.0625     0.200
## 4 Spinner D  0.25       0.17  0.0425     0.136</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>prior_post_plot(bayes_df)</code></pre>
